<DOC><DOCNO> AP881012-0243 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-12-88 1109EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-OPEC     10-12 0230</FIRST><SECOND>BC-OPEC,0240</SECOND><HEAD>OPEC Committee Meetings Scheduled In Madrid</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: Subroto, one name, is cq.</NOTE><DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two OPEC committees will meet in Madridon Oct.20, apparently to discuss tumbling oil prices at a time ofoverproduction and disarray in the world oil market, OPEC SecretaryGeneral Subroto announced Wednesday.   The announcement, carried by OPENA, the news agency of the13-member Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries, didnot provide an agenda or other details.   It said the two committees will hold their first joint meetingin the Spanish capital.   They are the Committee on Price Evolution, comprising the oilministers of Algeria, Indonesia, Nigeria, Saudi Arabia andVenezuela, and the Long-Term Strategy Committee consisting of theoil ministers of Algeria, Iran, Iraq, Kuwait, Saudi Arabia andVenezuela.   World oil prices have plunged recently, running more than $5 abarrel below the cartel's benchmark of $18 for a 42-gallon barrel.   Several OPEC member countries have considerably exceeded theirproduction quotas. Their conduct and longterm energy savingmeasures introduced in many industrialized countries have triggereda decline in prices.   Subroto said recently prices could plummet to $5 a barrel ifSaudi Arabia _ the world's largest oil exporter _ exploited itsproduction capacity to force other OPEC members to obsderve theirquotas.   A full ministerial conference of the organization is scheduledto take place in Vienna on Nov. 21.</TEXT></DOC>